          <!-- Full description -->
          <div class="col-lg-12">
            <div class="portfolio-description" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="300">
              <h2>WaitWell — Patient Communication &amp; Queue Management Platform</h2>
              <p>Hospital patients and their families often experience significant anxiety because they have no visibility into where they are in the care process — whether they're waiting for a doctor, a test, or discharge. WaitWell solves this by providing a real-time visit progress tracker that keeps patients informed at every step, reducing uncertainty and improving the overall care experience.</p>
              <p>As the full-stack developer and project maintainer, I was responsible for the complete architecture and implementation: the real-time dashboard, AI-powered health chat with per-user rate limiting, Supabase database schema with Row-Level Security, Stripe subscription billing, admin dashboard with RBAC, Web Push notifications, and a full CI/CD pipeline with automated testing on every PR.</p>

              <div class="features mt-4">
                <h3>Key Features</h3>
                <div class="row gy-3">
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="feature-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="400">
                      <i class="bi bi-person-check-fill"></i>
                      <h4>Multi-Role Authentication</h4>
                      <p>Patient and Admin roles via ASP.NET Core Identity with RBAC — each role sees only what they're permitted to access.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="feature-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="500">
                      <i class="bi bi-robot"></i>
                      <h4>AI Health Chat</h4>
                      <p>OpenRouter API (Claude model) with Vercel AI SDK — rate-limited per user to prevent abuse.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="feature-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="600">
                      <i class="bi bi-credit-card"></i>
                      <h4>Stripe Subscription Billing</h4>
                      <p>Gated subscription tiers managed through Stripe with webhook-driven access control.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-md-6">
                    <div class="feature-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="700">
                      <i class="bi bi-github"></i>
                      <h4>CI/CD &amp; Testing</h4>
                      <p>GitHub Actions pipeline with Vitest and React Testing Library — full unit test coverage of core logic and components.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="mt-4">
                <h3>Tech Stack</h3>
                <p>Next.js 16 (App Router) &bull; TypeScript &bull; Tailwind CSS v4 &bull; shadcn/ui &bull; Supabase (PostgreSQL + RLS + Auth) &bull; OpenRouter AI &bull; Vercel AI SDK &bull; Stripe &bull; Web Push API &bull; Vitest &bull; React Testing Library &bull; GitHub Actions &bull; ESLint &bull; Prettier &bull; Husky &bull; commitlint</p>
              </div>
            </div>
